                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/675.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Referring to the memorandum of the 16th ultimo by which the ambassador of Mexico
                    informed the Secretary of State of the activity of Mexican insurgents in El
                    Paso, Tex., and requested that proceedings be instituted against those found
                    guilty of violating the neutrality laws, the Secretary of State has the honor to
                    say that he is advised by the Attorney General under date of the 26th ultimo
                    that the information contained in the memorandum of the ambassador of Mexico has
                    been transmitted to the officers of the Department of Justice in the western
                    district of Texas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-02-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
